using namespace std;

namespace kindergarten_garden {

vector<string> plants(const string& diagram, const string& student) {
    // Fixed list of children in order
    vector<string> children = {
        "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "David", 
        "Eve", "Fred", "Ginny", "Harriet", 
        "Ileana", "Joseph", "Kincaid", "Larry"
    };
    
    // Find the index of the student
    int index = -1;
    for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); i++) {
        if (children[i] == student) {
            index = i;
            break;
        }
    }
    if (index == -1) {
        return {};
    }
    
    // Split the diagram into two rows
    size_t newline_pos = diagram.find('\n');
    string row1 = diagram.substr(0, newline_pos);
    string row2 = diagram.substr(newline_pos + 1);
    
    // Ensure the rows are long enough
    // Each child has 2 plants per row, so 12 children * 2 = 24 plants per row
    // But we'll just use the index to access
    
    // Get the starting positions for the child's plants in each row
    int start_pos = 2 * index;
    
    // Map the plant codes to their full names
    map<char, string> plant_map = {
        {'G', "grass"},
        {'C', "clover"},
        {'R', "radishes"},
        {'V', "violets"}
    };
    
    // Get all plants
    vector<string> result;
    result.push_back(plant_map[row1[start_pos]]);
    result.push_back(plant_map[row1[start_pos + 1]]);
    result.push_back(plant_map[row2[start_pos]]);
    result.push_back(plant_map[row2[start_pos + 1]]);
    
    return result;
}

}  // namespace kindergarten_garden
